==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gibbon
<hw>Gib"bon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>gibbon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any arboreal ape of
the genus <gen>Hylobates</gen>, of which many species and varieties
inhabit the East Indies and Southern Asia. They are tailless and without
cheek pouches, and have very long arms, adapted for climbing.</def></p>

<p><-- common subtypes --> <note>⟦hand⟧ The white-handed gibbon
(<spn>Hylobates lar</spn>), the crowned (<spn>H. pilatus</spn>), the
wou-wou or singing gibbon (<spn>H. agilis</spn>), the siamang, and the
hoolock. are the most common species.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gib boom</ent>⟦br⟧
